ng that &quot;post reply&quot; button =) <br><br>So, lemme cut and copy part of the response I am sending the first correspondent: <br><br>&quot;Levels 40 - 50 have been designed to be pretty long. Well, actually, really, really, really long. We wanted to break it up a little, reward people for getting through it. The main things about this change are the resetting of the death floor and the con point limit at the half mark, a change that was badly needed. Exp is so slow after 40 that it was making people insane to die - and the price of con points can break you (assuming you are a normal player without a wealthy guild backing your every move) if you take risks and die too often. That's no fun at all. This change alleviates that a great deal. <br><br>The difference between a 20 and a 30 is HUGE. It will be nearly impossibly hard for a 20 to beat a 30 in PVP. But 30 and 40 is a smaller difference, and 40 and 50 smaller still. <br><br>However - your letter brought up some excellent points regarding min-maxing, making characters ultimately less different, and so forth. An emergency meeting was held this morning, and the team has decided that we needed to revisit how many extra points a player would receive at the halfway mark. We decided the &quot;half levels&quot; will only get &quot;half points&quot; - ie, at level 40 and a half, the player will get 20 extra skill points instead of the 40 planned. At level 41, the player will get 41 new points. <br><br>This puts the min-max numbers, for a player who has three skills and one skill point per level, at 50 in one/22 in another/0 in the last, or 50/15/15, which you can see will really have a minimal long term impact, while still giving each player at the level step a slight improvement in their character (and once you get to that level, I think you'll agree that some sort of reward and bonus is certainly in order). <br><br>Thank you very much for your thoughtful criticism. It was ultimately very helpful.&quot; <br><br>Okay, now - I didn't do the math. One of the devs gave me the min/max numbers for a 1X class with three skills, so if the numbers are wrong, please post your math WITHOUT any comments regarding my stupidity :P <br><br>So, as you can see, Matt's comment was BEFORE the meeting. The numbers I just provided are the correct ones. <br><br>This will not have the impact you might think due to the narrowing of the level gap in combat. This will have utterly NO effect on high level PVE content, because as our critics have pointed out, we don't HAVE much content there yet. Therefore, anything we put in the game will be balanced with these half levels in mind. <br><br>But the long and short of it is you certainly did have an impact, and I appreciate the emails - I glance over the boards first thing, then do email, and then post. Our change in plans happened because y'all helped me to be on top of things. Thanks! <br> <p>----------<br>Friar Jaret<br>God bless the Grail Keepers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ujaretfure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaret Fure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mumbling Friar</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#993300>(10/25/01 12:00:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We're going to get more skill points!!!</span><hr size=1> And a follow up...<br><br>----------<br><br>Guys, <br><br>Some clarification. <br><br>First, please don't email Mark or Lori when you have gripes with the game. It is Sanya's job to pass on your criticism to the devs, not Mark's. <br><br>Second, here's the way the numbers work (assuming a mage &quot;1 point per level&quot; character): <br><br>40th level 40 points <br>40.5 20 points <br>41 41 points <br>41.5 20 points <br>42 42 points <br>42.5 21 points <br>...and so on <br><br>This means that you get essentially half your level's training points each half level. This is hardly unbalancing or reduces the &quot;uniqueness&quot; of a character. Instead it gives classes a little more &quot;wiggle room&quot; to flesh out skills that they otherwise might neglect. <br><br>An example: If you have a mage that has maxed out (at level 50) one of his skills, then this gives him the ability (with his 220 extra spec points) to take ONE other skill to around 20th level; or both other skills to around 13th level. This means if you are the unique fire mage, and you see an ice mage at level 50 speccing in fire, he'll only be able to get 20th level spells. <br><br>The intent of this was not to make classes less unique, it was to lessen brutal nature of the long curve between levels after level 40 by giving you some extra spice. <br><br>Matt F <br>Mythic Entertainment <br> <p>----------<br>Friar Jaret<br>God bless the Grail Keepers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ugalendril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galendril</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Follow the bard dammit!!!</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#993300>(10/25/01 12:12:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/fforgottengrailkeepersfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We're going to get more skill points!!!</span><hr size=1> I think this is great news.  It gives folks a little room to experiment at lower levels without feeling like they've screwed thier character for the end game.<br><br>I've put points into stealth.  Now I don't have to worry that I won't be able to max out songs.  This 